The paper discusses the use of auto-encoders as building blocks of deep network classifiers, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and specifically falls under the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on improving the performance of auto-encoders by eliminating task-irrelevant input variables, which is related to the sub-categories of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses experimental results on challenging datasets, which is related to the sub-categories of "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) and "cs.CL" (Computation and Language).
